Slowly and cautiously...[p]
Confirming each step as I go, I descend the staircase to a mad place in which light cannot reach.[p]
Finally I reach a wide room, much wider than I imagined.[p]
I guess this based on the echoes of my footsteps.[p]
I am running.[p]
Through this eerie space that lies in the basement of the basement of the hospital.[p]
It is lifeless, and there is no light.[p]
All I can do is run through it.[p]
Does this world have an end? [p]
Or did it even have a beginning?[p]
Everywhere I go, all that I do, is solve the mysteries that appear one after the other and then move on...[p]
I understand this, and expect that the same situation will continue.[p]
Still, all I can do is move forward.[p]
My thinking always results in this conclusion.[p]


